## Example 4 — Probability from a Frequency Table

A survey of 200 students asks about their favorite subject:

| Subject | Frequency |
|---------|-----------|
| Math | 60 |
| Science | 50 |
| English | 45 |
| History | 30 |
| Art | 15 |

Find the probability that a randomly selected student chose Math.

### Step 1: Total Number of Outcomes

$$|S| = 60 + 50 + 45 + 30 + 15 = 200$$

### Step 2: Favorable Outcomes (Math)

$$|\text{Math}| = 60$$

### Step 3: Compute Probability

$$P(\text{Math}) = \frac{60}{200} = \frac{3}{10} = 0.3$$

### Step 4: Find the Complement

$$P(\text{not Math}) = 1 - 0.3 = 0.7$$

### Step 5: Verify

All probabilities should sum to 1:

$$\frac{60 + 50 + 45 + 30 + 15}{200} = \frac{200}{200} = 1 \checkmark$$

✅ Answer: $P(\text{Math}) = \frac{3}{10} = 30\%$

