## Example 5 — Real-World: Weather Forecast Probability

A 10-day forecast shows the following rain probabilities:

| Day | P(rain) |
|-----|---------|
| 1 | 0.8 |
| 2 | 0.6 |
| 3 | 0.4 |
| 4 | 0.3 |
| 5 | 0.2 |

(a) On which day is it most likely to rain?
(b) Find $P(\text{no rain})$ on Day 3.
(c) Find the probability it rains on Day 1 but not Day 2 (assuming independence).

### Step 1: Most Likely Day

Day 1 has $P(\text{rain}) = 0.8$, the highest probability.

### Step 2: Complement on Day 3

$$P(\text{no rain, Day 3}) = 1 - 0.4 = 0.6$$

### Step 3: Independent Events (Preview)

$$P(\text{rain Day 1 AND not rain Day 2}) = 0.8 \times 0.4 = 0.32$$

✅ Answer: (a) Day 1 ($P = 0.8$); (b) $P(\text{no rain, Day 3}) = 0.6$; (c) $P = 0.32 = 32\%$

